 |dead-url     = no
}}</ref>

== 公司概况 ==
=== 领导层 ===
康卡斯特集团在有些时候会被认为是家族企业。<ref name=vision>{{cite journal
 |last         = Pearlstine
 |first        = Norman
 |title        = Brian Roberts on His Vision for Comcast
 |journal      = Bloomberg Businessweek
 |date         = 2012-08-09
 |url          = http://www.businessweek.com/articles/2012-08-09/brian-roberts-on-his-vision-for-comcast
 |accessdate   = 2014-03-26
 |quote        = Comcast (CMCSA) is a 49-year-old family company that morphed into a media behemoth with the 2011 purchase of NBCUniversal.
 |archive-date = 2014-09-16
 |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20140916140436/http://www.businessweek.com/articles/2012-08-09/brian-roberts-on-his-vision-for-comcast
 |dead-url     = no
}}</ref> 集团董事长、总裁兼首席执行官{{Link-en|布莱恩·L·罗伯茨|Brian L. Roberts}}是集团联合创始人{{Link-en|拉尔夫·J·罗伯茨|Ralph J. Roberts}}的儿子。罗伯茨家庭拥有或控制大约1%的集团股份，但这些股份全都是B类超级投票权股份，这使得布莱恩在董事会上拥有“不可逾越的33%投票权”。<ref name=note>All of Comcast's class B common stock, which controls 33.3% of voting power, is owned by CEO Brian Roberts. (see {{cite web
 |url          = http://www.cmcsk.com/secfiling.cfm?filingID=950159-04-860
 |title        = Form S-3 pp.10
 |publisher    = Comcast
 |date         = 2004-09-21
 |accessdate   = 2014-03-21
 |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20141217040438/http://www.cmcsk.com/secfiling.cfm?filingID=950159-04-860
 |archive-date = 2014-12-17
 |dead-url     = yes
}})</ref> 法律专家{{Link-en|苏珊·P·克劳福德|Susan P. Crawford}}表示这使得布莱恩“对（康卡斯特）每一步都有有效的控制”。<ref name=Crawford>{{cite book
  | last      = Crawford
  | first     = Susan
  | title     = Captive Audience : the telecom industry and monopoly power in the new gilded age
  | year      = 2013
  | publisher = Yale University Press
  | page      = 67
  | url       = https://books.google.com/?id=G4KCPGnKFEUC&printsec=frontcover&dq=captive+audience+crawford#v=onepage&q=captive%20audience%20crawford&f=false
  | isbn     = 0300167377
  }}</ref> 2010年，布莱恩已经是全美薪酬最高的公司高管之一，其年薪高达3,100万美元。<ref name=Crawford/>

=== 办公处 ===
康卡斯特集团的总部位于[[美国|美国]][[宾夕法尼亚州|宾夕法尼亚州]]的[[费城|费城]]，并同时在[[亚特兰大|亚特兰大]]、[[底特律|底特律]]、[[丹佛|丹佛]]、[[曼徹斯特_(新罕布什爾州)|曼彻斯特]]和[[纽约市|纽约市]]设有公司办事处。<ref>[http://www.comcast.com/corporate/about/pressroom/corporateoverview/corporateoverview.html Comcast Corporate Overview] {{Wayback|url=http://www.comcast.com/corporate/about/pressroom/corporateoverview/corporateoverview.html |date=20081006052044 }}. Comcast.com. Retrieved on 2011-07-08.</ref> 2005年1月3日，康卡斯特集团宣布将成为费城市中心[[康卡斯特中心|康卡斯特中心]]的主要租户。这栋高达{{convert|297|m|ft}}的[[摩天大楼|摩天大楼]]是宾夕法尼亚州的最高建筑。2014年夏天，康卡斯特集团在原集团总部直接相邻的地方开始修建第二栋高达{{convert|342|m|ft}}的[[康卡斯特科技中心|摩天大楼]]。<ref>{{cite web
 |url          = http://articles.philly.com/2014-01-17/news/46268087_1_comcast-corp-new-building-comcast-center
 |title        = Comcast to build second, taller Phila. skyscraper
 |website      = The Philadelphia Inquirer
 |author       = Bob Fernandez
 |date         = 2014-01-17
 |accessdate   = 2014-03-27
 |archive-date = 2014-02-19
 |archive-url  = https://archive.today/20140219005307/http://articles.philly.com/2014-01-17/news/46268087_1_comcast-corp-new-building-comcast-center
 |dead-url     = no
}}</ref>

=== 劳资关系 ===
媒体及康卡斯特集团的员工经常批评集团对劳资关系政策的暧昧。2012年，一篇由康卡斯特集团呼叫中心员工匿名发布在[[Reddit|Reddit]]的帖子以强烈的语气向公众分享了他们在康卡斯特工作的消极体验，而这篇帖子引发了诸如《[[赫芬顿邮报|赫芬顿邮报]]》等媒体的关注。<ref>{{cite web
  | title      = Comcast Employee Tells World He Hates His Job In Reddit AMA Post
  | url      = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/09/19/comcast-employee-tells-world-he-hates-his-job-reddit-ama_n_1897425.html
  | website      = The Huffington Post
  | accessdate      = 2015-01-16
  | archive-date      = 2017-09-15
  | archive-url      = https://web.archive.org/web/20170915072450/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/09/19/comcast-employee-tells-world-he-hates-his-job-reddit-ama_n_1897425.html
  | dead-url      = no
  }}</ref> 2014年，由[[The_Verge|The Verge]]发布的调查系列采访了150名康卡斯特集团的员工。它试图研究康卡斯特集团为何受到客户、媒体乃至其雇员的广泛批评。该报道系列声称造成现状的部分原因是康卡斯特集团的内部因素，因为其员工正在承受公司的不合理政策。据报道，“（康卡斯特集团）的客服服务已经被销售困扰所取代；技术人员人手不足且技术支持人员的培训不足；公司正备受内部分裂的困扰。”<ref>{{cite web
  | title      = To Understand Comcast's Lousy Reputation
  | url      = http://www.philly.com/philly/blogs/inq-phillydeals/Inside-Comcast-customer-service.html
  | website      = The Philadelphia Inquirer
  | accessdate      = 2015-01-16
  | archive-date      = 2017-09-15
  | archive-url      = https://web.archive.org/web/20170915070422/http://www.philly.com/philly/blogs/inq-phillydeals/Inside-Comcast-customer-service.html
  | dead-url      = no
  }}</ref> 2014年11月，由另外一名康卡斯特集团客户服务中心的员工所匿名发布在{{Link-en|Cracked.com|Cracked.com}}的帖子引发了广泛阅读。这篇名为《当你为全美最差公司工作时的五大噩梦》声称康卡斯特集团痴迷于销售业绩，而没有对员工进行足够充分的培训，并声称“这套系统并不能为客户提供良好的服务”。<ref>{{cite web
  | title      = Five Nightmares You Live While Working For America's Worst Company
  | url      = http://www.cracked.com/article_21756_5-reasons-working-comcast-worse-than-you-think_p2.html
  | publisher      = Cracked
  | accessdate      = 2015-01-16
  | archive-date      = 2014-12-29
  | archive-url      = https://web.archive.org/web/20141229103222/http://www.cracked.com/article_21756_5-reasons-working-comcast-worse-than-you-think_p2.html
  | dead-url      = no
  }}</ref>

康卡斯特集团因其反工会的政策而知名。根据该集团的一本员工培训手册的说法，“康卡斯特不认为工会代表符合其员工、客户和股东的最佳利益”。<ref>{{cite news
 |url          = https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/articles/A64667-2004Sep5.html
 |title        = Union Rights Triumph Over Intimidation
 |website      = The New York Times
 |author       = Cameron W. Barr
 |date         = 2004-09-06
 |accessdate   = 2014-02-27
 |archive-date = 2021-02-16
 |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20210216230515/https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/articles/A64667-2004Sep5.html
 |dead-url     = no
}}</ref> 2014年，代表大部分在[[俄勒冈州|俄勒冈州]][[比佛頓市_(俄勒岡州)|比弗顿]]康卡斯特集团员工利益的{{Link-en|美国电讯工人联合会|Communications Workers of America}}与集团发生争执，集团管理层威胁员工，要求他们参加反工会集会并对工会成员处以不必要的纪律处分。<ref>[http://www.nwlaborpress.org/2004/8-6-04CWA.html, Comcast Systematically Squeezing Out Unions] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nwlaborpress.org/2004/8-6-04CWA.html, |date=20040830073028 }}, Northwest Labor Press, 2004.</ref> 2011年，康卡斯特集团受到了[[美国编剧工会|美国编剧工会]]对其工会政策的批评。<ref>[http://www.thewrap.com/media/article/comcast-seeking-%E2%80%98-destroy%E2%80%99-writers-guild-claims-board-members-24898?page=0, Comcast Seeking to Destroy Writer's Guild, Members Say] {{Wayback|url=http://www.thewrap.com/media/article/comcast-seeking-%E2%80%98-destroy%E2%80%99-writers-guild-claims-board-members-24898?page=0, |date=20130628185009 }}, CNN's the Wrap, 2011.</ref>

尽管有上述批评，但是康卡斯特集团也依旧在数个“最佳工作场所”排名里榜上有名。2009年，《{{lang|en|CableFAX}}》杂志将康卡斯特列为“有线行业十大工作场所”，称赞其“规模、精明和远见”。<ref>[http://www.cablefax.com/programming/networks/2009-Top-10-Places-to-Work-in-Cable_38104.html 2009 Top 10 Places to Work in Cable] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20130118151405/http://www.cablefax.com/programming/networks/2009-Top-10-Places-to-Work-in-Cable_38104.html |date=2013-01-18 }}, CableFAX, 2009-10-27.</ref> 无独有偶，《{{Link-en|费城商业期刊|Philadelphia Business Journal}}》授予康卡斯特集团为费城特大公司银牌，而金牌得主则是康卡斯特集团旗下的子公司{{Link-en|康卡斯特演出|Comcast Spectacor}}。<ref>[http://philadelphia.bizjournals.com/philadelphia/stories/2009/10/19/focus3.html Silver Winner - Extra-Large Company Comcast Corp.] {{Wayback|url=http://philadelphia.bizjournals.com/philadelphia/stories/2009/10/19/focus3.html |date=20091106050358 }}, Philadelphia Business Journal, 2009-10-16.</ref><ref>[http://philadelphia.bizjournals.com/philadelphia/stories/2009/10/19/focus2.html?q=%20best%20places%20to%20work%20%20philadelphia%20comcast Gold Winner - Extra-Large Company: Comcast-Spectacor], Philadelphia Business Journal, 2009-10-16.</ref> 2009年，《[[波士顿环球报|波士顿环球报]]》发现康卡斯特是费城最佳工作场所。<ref>[http://www.boston.com/jobs/topworkplaces/2009/articles/a_cable_company_that_listens/ A cable company that listens] {{Wayback|url=http://www.boston.com/jobs/topworkplaces/2009/articles/a_cable_company_that_listens/ |date=20210320115816 }}, The Boston Globe, 2009-11-08.</ref> 员工多样性也是康卡斯特集团的一个强烈标志。2008年，《{{Link-en|黑人企业|Black Enterprise}}》杂志将康卡斯特列为员工多样性公司的前15名。<ref>[http://www.blackenterprise.com/diversity/diversity-lists/2008/07/10/the-15-best-companies-for-workforce-diversity-2 The 15 Best Companies for Workforce Diversity] {{Wayback|url=http://www.blackenterprise.com/diversity/diversity-lists/2008/07/10/the-15-best-companies-for-workforce-diversity-2 |date=20091218083520 }}, Black Enterprise, 2008-07-10.</ref> 康卡斯特还被《华盛顿邮报》在其年度特刊上评选为“2014年度最佳工作场所”。<ref>{{cite web
 |title        = The Washington Post Top Workplaces 2014
 |url          = http://www.topworkplaces.com/frontend.php/regional-list/list/washington
 |website      = www.topworkplaces.com
 |publisher    = The Washington Post Magazine
 |accessdate   = 2014-08-06
 |archive-date = 2017-09-15
 |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20170915070403/http://www.topworkplaces.com/frontend.php/regional-list/list/washington
 |dead-url     = no
}}</ref> [[人权战线|人权战线]]给康卡斯特的企业平等指数（{{lang|en|Corporate Equality Index}}）打分为100；<ref>{{Cite web
 |url          = http://hrc-assets.s3-website-us-east-1.amazonaws.com//files/assets/resources/CEI-2017-FinalReport.pdf
 |title        = Corporate Equality Index 2017
 |last         = 
 |first        = 
 |date         = 
 |website      = www.hrc.org/
 |publisher    = Human Rights Campaign
 |access-date  = 2013-12-16
 |archive-date = 2016-12-20
 |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20161220205645/http://hrc-assets.s3-website-us-east-1.amazonaws.com//files/assets/resources/CEI-2017-FinalReport.pdf
 |dead-url     = no
}}</ref> 同时也认为它是[[LGBT|LGBT]]人群的最佳工作场所之一。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hrc.org/resources/best-places-to-work-2017|title=Best Places to Work 2017 {{!}} Human Rights Campaign|last=Campaign|first=Human Rights|website=Human Rights Campaign|access-date=2016-12-13|archive-date=2019-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190412205627/https://www.hrc.org/resources/best-places-to-work-2017|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 财务表现 ===
康卡斯特集团股票从1999年的每股8.19[[美元|美元]]增加至2009年的每股15美元，其账面价值增长近一倍；而[[營業額|收入]]也从1999年的60亿美元增加了六倍，达到了2009年的近360亿美元；[[淨利率|净利润率]]也从1999年的4.2%提升至2009年的8.4%；经营利润率提高了31%；而股本回报率则在同一时间翻至6.7%。而在1999年到2009年之间，集团资本回报率增加了近2倍，达到了7%。<ref name="autogenerated2">[http://www.sj-r.com/business/x1992007274/Malcom-Berko-Taking-stock Malcolm Berko: Taking stock] {{Wayback|url=http://www.sj-r.com/business/x1992007274/Malcom-Berko-Taking-stock |date=20130309160654 }}, The State Journal-Register, 2009-10-07.</ref> 根据康卡斯特集团的报告声称，在2012年第一季度，由于高速宽带网络用户的增加，其利润增长幅度高达30%。<ref>{{cite news
  | url       = http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/entertainmentnewsbuzz/2012/05/comcast-corp-earnings-.html
  | title       = Comcast profit jumps 30%, with mixed results at NBCUniversal
  | work       = Los Angeles Times
  | date       = 2012-05-02
  | accessdate       = 2013-03-03
  | archive-date       = 2021-10-19
  | archive-url       = https://web.archive.org/web/20211019040343/https://latimesblogs.latimes.com/entertainmentnewsbuzz/2012/05/comcast-corp-earnings-.html
  | dead-url       = no
  }}</ref> 2014年，由于2月所举行的[[2014年冬季奥林匹克运动会|索契奥运会]]的缘故，康卡斯特集团在第一季度创造了11亿美元的收入。<ref>[https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/04/22/us-comcast-idUSBREA3L0KP20140422 Reuters] {{Wayback|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/04/22/us-comcast-idUSBREA3L0KP20140422 |date=20151018030107 }} 2014-042-22 Reuters</ref>

=== 游说及政治捐款 ===
康卡斯特集团在2013年度为[[游说集团|政治游说]]花费了1,880万[[美元|美元]]，是美国单个公司或组织政治游说预算花销的第七高。<ref name=TopSpenders>{{cite web
  | url        = https://www.opensecrets.org/lobby/top.php?showYear=2013&indexType=s
  | title        = Lobbying: Top Spenders 2013
  | publisher        = Center for Responsive Politics
  | accessdate        = 2014-02-21
  | archive-date        = 2019-06-13
  | archive-url        = https://web.archive.org/web/20190613030442/http://www.opensecrets.org/lobby/top.php?indexType=s&showYear=2013
  | dead-url        = no
  }}</ref> 集团雇佣了多名前[[美国国会|国会议员]]为说客。<ref name=Web>{{cite news
 |url          = https://www.nytimes.com/2014/02/21/business/media/comcasts-web-of-lobbying-and-philanthropy.html?rref=technology
 |title        = Comcast’s Web of Lobbying and Philanthropy
 |website      = The New York Times
 |author       = Eric Lipton
 |date         = 2014-02-20
 |accessdate   = 2014-02-21
 |archive-date = 2021-02-16
 |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20210216230619/https://www.nytimes.com/2014/02/21/business/media/comcasts-web-of-lobbying-and-philanthropy.html?rref=technology
 |dead-url     = no
}}</ref>  {{Link-en|美国国家有线电视与电信协会|National Cable & Telecommunications Association}}是美国第五大游说组织，其董事会拥有多名康卡斯特集团高管，同时它也是代表以康卡斯特集团为代表的美国有线电视产业；美国国家有线电视与电信协会在2013年度的游说花费高达1,980万美元。<ref name=TopSpenders /> 康卡斯特集团是[[贝拉克·奥巴马|贝拉克·奥巴马]]竞选[[美国总统|美国总统]]时的最大支持者之一，集团副总裁{{Link-en|戴维·L·科昂|David L. Cohen|戴维·科昂}}在2007年到2012年度为其募款220多万美元。<ref>{{cite news
 |url          = https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2012/09/13/us/politics/obamas-top-fund-raisers.html?_r=1&
