=== 职业运动 ===
{{Main|康卡斯特演出}}

1996年，康卡斯特集团从演出公司（Spectacor）创始人{{Link-en|艾德·施耐德|Ed Snider}}手里买下了公司的控股权。<ref>{{cite web
 |url          = http://articles.philly.com/1996-03-22/sports/25637786_1_comcast-move-flyers-and-sixers-msg-network
 |title        = Msg What Comcast Hopes To Become
 |website      = The Philadelphia Inquirer
 |author       = Bill Fleischman
 |date         = 2996-03-22
 |accessdate   = 2014-02-16
 |archive-date = 2016-03-04
 |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304080634/http://articles.philly.com/1996-03-22/sports/25637786_1_comcast-move-flyers-and-sixers-msg-network
 |dead-url     = no
}}</ref> 康卡斯特演出公司目前的控股资产包括[[国家冰球联盟|国家冰球联盟]]球队[[費城飛人|费城飞人队]]及其在[[费城|费城]]的主场体育馆。多年来，康卡斯特集团成为{{Link-en|NBC地区体育电视网|NBC Sports Regional Networks|康卡斯特体育电视网}}、[[高尔夫台|高尔夫台]]和[[NBCSN|NBCSN]]（曾先后用名“户外生活电视网（{{lang|en|Outdoor Life Network}}）”和“对抗频道（{{lang|en|Versus}}）”）的主要股权拥有者。2002年，康卡斯特集团向[[马里兰大学|马里兰大学]]支付了2,500万美元，用于购买其[[马里兰大学帕克分校|帕克分校]]校区里新建篮球馆的[[冠名权|冠名权]]。新球馆被命名为“{{Link-en|XFINITY中心 (马里兰大学帕克分校)|Xfinity Center (College Park, Maryland)|XFINITY中心}}”，但在2002年建成开馆到2014年7月期间，这个球馆最初被命名为“康卡斯特中心”。

=== 风险投资 ===
康卡斯特集团于1999年1月成立该集团的第一支[[风险投资|风险投资]][[基金|基金]]——康卡斯特互动资本（{{lang|en|Comcast Interactive Capital}}）。<ref>{{cite news
 |url          = http://www.bizjournals.com/philadelphia/stories/1999/07/05/story2.html
 |title        = Comcast: Not just cable anymore
 |publisher    = Philadelphia Business Journal
 |author       = Peter Key
 |date         = 1999-07-05
 |accessdate   = 2014-02-21
 |archive-date = 2017-09-15
 |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20170915070739/https://www.bizjournals.com/philadelphia/stories/1999/07/05/story2.html
 |dead-url     = no
}}</ref> 在2011年前后，继集团收购了[[NBC环球|NBC环球]]之后，康卡斯特互动资本与NBC环球旗下的风投子公司孔雀股权基金（{{lang|en|The Peacock Equity Fund}}）合并。<ref>{{cite web
 |url          = http://www.multichannel.com/content/comcast-nbcu-combine-venture-capital-units
 |title        = Comcast, NBCU Combine Venture Capital Units
 |publisher    = MultiChannel News
 |author       = Mike Farrell
 |date         = 2011-05-26
 |accessdate   = 2014-02-21
 |archive-date = 2014-02-28
 |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20140228022659/http://www.multichannel.com/content/comcast-nbcu-combine-venture-capital-units
 |dead-url     = no
}}</ref> 合并后的公司起名为“康卡斯特风险投资（{{lang|en|Comcast Ventures}}）”，目前这件公司投资的企业包括{{Link-en|FanDuel|FanDuel}}、{{Link-en|Vox传媒|Vox Media}}等。<ref>{{cite news
 |url          = https://www.forbes.com/sites/darrenheitner/2013/01/30/fantasy-sports-service-fanduel-secures-11-million-investment-includes-money-from-comcast-ventures/
 |title        = Fantasy Sports Service, FanDuel, Secures $11 Million Investment; Includes Money From Comcast Ventures
 |publisher    = Forbes
 |author       = Darren Heitner
 |date         = 2013-01-30
 |accessdate   = 2014-02-16
 |archive-date = 2021-02-16
 |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20210216230905/https://www.forbes.com/sites/darrenheitner/2013/01/30/fantasy-sports-service-fanduel-secures-11-million-investment-includes-money-from-comcast-ventures/
 |dead-url     = no
}}</ref><ref>{{cite web
 |url         = http://philadelphia.citybizlist.com/article/comcast-ventures-backed-vox-media-raises-34-million
 |title       = Comcast Ventures-backed Vox Media Raises $34 Million
